Author: Sdunbar#5064
Content: Any news on the rebrand? Seems its being going on a very long time

Author: Audo#5667
Content:
Hey Sdunbar, thanks for asking. I would say there are three components that all must be finished. 
1) We have few different dev projects going on simultaniously, for example few weeks ago we gave this sneak peak: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=TaH8oR5nXpg
2) Business & product strategies have to be finalized
3) Marketing messaging & branding has to be completed

We have done good progress on all aspects, but none of them is finished ‚Äì and they all must be fully finished for us to go online with the rebrand.

Expect it all to still take time. We are not rushing this as it's important for our long term success. Our rebrand is not about marketing, but more developing a product and business development.

Author: Daniel CP#2020
Content: Many reasons. The rebrand is about much more than just a new logo and a new website. We're releasing a few new products and want to really redefine Komodo to accompany the go-to-market

Author: Daniel CP#2020
Content: It's about re-introducing Komodo to the industry in general. The rebrand will include new logo, new colors, new messaging, and new website, but all of that is really just to support and draw as much as attention as possible to the new tech and finished products

Content: A new multi-coin wallet, an automated blockchain generator web app hosted on AWS Marketplace and, a little further down the road, v2 of Komodo's atomic swap DEX
